= Cleaning up older versions =

Normally older versions could be cleaned up using <tt>sudo gem cleanup</tt> as described in "[[Removing older versions of installed gems]]". This won't work for [[ZenTest]] because up until [[ZenTest 3.5.0]] the [[gem]] was named <tt>zentest-3.5.0</tt> (all lowercase) whereas subsequent versions where named in [[CamelCase]] (<tt>ZenTest-3.6.0</tt>). As such, doing a <tt>sudo gem cleanup</tt> will leave both [[ZenTest 3.6.0]] ''and'' [[ZenTest 3.5.0]] on your system; it is necessary to manually uninstall [[ZenTest 3.5.0]] in this case:

<pre># explicitly specify version, just in case
sudo gem uninstall zentest --version '3.5.0'</pre>

